features: 24 Pin motherboard power extension cable features one male and one female 24 Pin ATX connector, extending the length of your ATX power supply connection
This 24-pin CPU extension cable extends the power connector from a ATX power supply to a motherboard power connection to provide strain relief on the connections of your computer case components
It is 12.6 inch (32cm) in length, giving you enough space within the computer case
Motherboard extension cable has removable cable ties for dressing the cable and a clip and latch for a secure connection to prevent accidental disconnections
ATX 24 Pin Motherboard Power Extension Cable, 12.6 Inches / 32cm, Internal PC PSU ATX 24 Pin Male to 24 Pin Female Extension Power Cable
body.description: Specifications: Cable color: black Connector1: 5557 24pin (20+4) male connector Connector2: 5559 24pin female connector Cable length : 12.6 inches / 32cm Cable type: 1007 18AWG Cable material: tinned copper Insulation material: PVC insulation Wire outer diameter: OD2.1mm Rated temperature: 80 degrees Applications: 1. Extend the length of an ATX power supply connection by up to 12.6inch. 2. Extends the length of ATX 2.01 motherboard power supply cable. 3. Ideal for tower cases. 4. Designed for all ATX 2.01 style motherboards. Package Includes: 1pcs ATX 24 Pin Motherboard Power Extension Cables

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 9, 2024
reviews.reviewText: Works perfectly. Case is a bottom mount for the PSU so I needed an extra length of supply cable. It doesn't match the finish but let's be real, you're not buying a black cord to see if for it's sheen and color. 10/10 hides easily and doesn't take any visual away from the internal LEDs and other more cosmetic components

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on November 15, 2020
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Perfect for needed extra length !
reviews.reviewText: Great extension cable for those custom builds that need an extra long main power cable ! Good quality and great value!

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 14, 2019
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Simple, does the job
reviews.reviewText: I needed a cable extension for my mother's PC, since cable management in her case is not ideal and a bit of a tight fit. The PSU cable on its own was not quite long enough to route the way I wanted, and this extension does the job. The cheap case I got for her happens to have a window, and I needed something that was inexpensive yet did not look as ugly as ketchup & mustard cables. It matches the black & blue motherboard & black interior of the case without the additional cost of sleeved cables.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on September 5, 2020
reviews.reviewTitle: 4.0 out of 5 stars Looks and works great, easy to use. Wires a little on the thin side.
reviews.reviewText: Looks and works great. My PSU cable was just too short to reach the MB. This extended it enough I could tuck it away for a cleaner install. More flexible than the PSU's cables.Wires are slightly thinner than the PSU's, but that might just be thinner insulation, to allow for more flexibility. Have had no issues with power delivery to my Xeon CPU.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on June 17, 2020
reviews.reviewText: I've been having problems with a Corsair power supply connected to my motherboard for a long time. Basically, the fit is poor and my voltage readings fluctuate significantly, which I believe to be the root cause for various problems I was having with the system.The female connector on this extension was very tight into the PSU connector - I am not able to wiggle it. Likewise, the male side is tight into the motherboard.Previously, I'd be able to wiggle the PSU connector on the MB and see variation in voltage measured by monitoring software or in the BIOS, but with this installed, so far, it's rock solid, and essentially has saved me from the need to replace the power supply.
